Currently, our Resources class is used for both the task resources requirement and cluster resources. To clarify them, we may want to create two subclass of the Resources class like the following:
```
class Resources # Our original Resources class

class TaskResources(Resources):
    def from_resources(other: Resources):
        pass
class ClusterResources(Resources)
```

During the task creation, we can convert the Resources specified by the user with `TaskResources.from_resources(resources)`.

